{{Unreferenced|date=February 2011}}

A '''foreline''' is a [[vacuum]] line between the [[pump]]s of a [[wikt:multistage|multistage]] vacuum system. No longer exclusively used by [[scientist]]s in [[research]], vacuum systems are used in numerous industries that include [[food production]] and the [[manufacture|manufacturing]] of [[electronic component]]s. A classic foreline is a [[hose]] or [[Pneumatic tube|tube]] that connects a [[rotary vane pump]] to the [[wikt:outlet|outlet]] of an [[oil diffusion pump]], although vacuum [[technology]] now uses a vast array of [[roughing pump]]s and high [[vacuum pump]]s.

Although the term has been used for many [[decade]]s in the high vacuum system [[industry]] and in [[literature]] concerning vacuum systems, the word foreline has not yet been added to any [[dictionary]].

